<Content>Worthy of all these 5 Star reviews My stay at the Hotel Colomba was so enjoyable that I wanted to both commend and recommend it to others. However, I see this was not an original idea. Everything you've read is true. The rooms are nice and the price is fair. The breakfast was one of the better ones. It's central location is fantastic (easy walk to Il Duomo, San Lorenzo Market, Uffizi, Ponte Vechio). The family who runs it is extremely friendly and helpful (ask for their recommendation on bisteca fiorentina), etc. But the one thing I want to add (and which had originally prompted me to write) was how great they were w/ our daughter. My wife and I stayed here w/ our 16 month old and they treated her like their own grandchild w/ lots of attention. They genuinely made sure that HER stay was enjoyable as well, such as by always having milk available any time it was needed. Our time in Florence was truly enhanced staying here and we would gladly recommend it to anyone. 
